wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9e093b26" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">disclosure</a> says that Circle has 61% of it=
s assets in =E2=80=9Ccash and cash equivalents,=E2=80=9D though that includ=
es not just bank accounts but also government money market funds and =E2=80=
=9Csecurities with an original maturity less than or equal to 90 days.=E2=
=80=9D The rest includes certificates of deposit, U.S. Treasuries, commerci=
al paper and corporate bonds. It is not obviously a super-aggressive mix or=
