; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">the report</a>. Again it does=C2=A0not seem super-aggressive or a=
nything, and you can see where they=E2=80=99re coming from. Both Circle=E2=
=80=99s and Tether=E2=80=99s reports are light on detail, but I think that =
if you read them with a reasonable amount of charity you will not come away=
 thinking =E2=80=9Cthese people are stretching wildly for yield, gambling t=
heir investors=E2=80=99 money on crazy assets.=E2=80=9D They=E2=80=99re buy=
ing commercial paper, whatever, that is what you do with a pot of money tha=
t you want to be worth $1. Still they have not always been great at=C2=A0<e=
m>saying that</em>.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" =
